# Project Rules for Cursor AI

## Changelog Requirements

When making changes to this project, ALWAYS update the CHANGELOG.md file:

1. **Include the "Requested" section**: Document what the user asked for, including:
   - The original request/question
   - Any specific considerations or constraints mentioned
   - Context about why the change was needed

2. **Format**: Use the standard format with sections:
   - Requested (what user asked for)
   - Added (new features)
   - Changed (modifications)
   - Deprecated (soon-to-be removed)
   - Removed (deleted features)
   - Fixed (bug fixes)
   - Security (security improvements)

3. **Timestamps**: Use [YYYY-MM-DD] format for dates

4. **Location**: Add new entries at the TOP of the changelog, under [Unreleased] or a new date section

5. **Details**: Be specific about what was changed, including file paths and folder structures

## Project Structure

- HTML pages go in `pages/` folder
- Assets go in `assets/` folder:
  - `assets/images/logos/` - Logo files
  - `assets/images/screenshots/` - Reference screenshots
  - `assets/images/content/` - Content images
  - `assets/css/` - Stylesheets
  - `assets/js/` - JavaScript files
  - `assets/data/google-sheets/` - Google Sheets documentation
  - `assets/data/references/` - PDFs and reference files
- Reusable HTML components in `partials/` folder
- Old/temp files in `archive/` folder

## Code Style

- Use semantic HTML
- Keep CSS in external files when possible
- Use relative paths from `pages/` directory (e.g., `../assets/css/styles.css`)
- Sidebar navigation is loaded dynamically via `sidebar-loader.js`
- Common CSS is in `assets/css/styles.css`

## Documentation

- Update relevant README files when adding new features
- Document Google Sheets usage in `assets/data/google-sheets/README.md`
- Keep CHANGELOG.md up to date with all changes

## File Paths

- When referencing assets from pages, use: `../assets/...`
- When referencing pages from sidebar, use: `../pages/pageX.html`
- When referencing partials from pages, use: `../partials/...`

